If I think I understand, then you can make use of the blend modes and layers:

```csharp
// get the image that we want to use as the "stroke"
var image = SKImage.FromEncodedData(SKData.Create("baboon.png"));

// create a paint that describes how the picture should be drawn
// basically use the image as the color instead of what was in the SVG
var paint = new SkPaint {
  ImageFilter = SKImageFilter.CreateBlendMode(SKBlendMode.DstIn, SKImageFilter.CreateImage(image))
};

// save the layer, and let SkiaSharp know that the paint is going to override something
canvas.SaveLayer(paint);

// draw the SVG as normal (on to the new layer)
canvas.DrawPicture(svg.Picture, ref matrix);

// apply the layer to the main canvas, through the paint
canvas.Restore();
```

Let me know if this is what you were trying to do.
